Model Structure Analysis Token Analysis Type Subset Analysis

About the country

Addresses in Australia typically follow the structure described in the following DOCUMENT.

Overview of concepts

name (freq: 38) - Full name
given-name (freq: 442) - Given namen (in Western cultures the first name)
additional-name - Additional given name (in Western cultures the middle name)
family-name (freq: 443) - Family name (in Western cultures the last name)
organization-title (freq: 1) - Title of a person within an organization
 
address - Address of a physical location - Artificial concept, not to be used in HTML
street-address (freq: 85) - Street address (street and location within the street)
address-line1 (freq: 417) - 1st line of street-address
address-line2 (freq: 419) - 2nd line of street-address
address-line3 (freq: 7) - 3rd line of street-address
address-line4 - 4th line of street-address
street-address-alternative-1 - Artificial concept, not to be used in HTML; this is a structured representation of a street address
building-location (freq: 2) - Name of a street and identifier for the building
street (freq: 9) - Name of a street
building (freq: 5) - House number
in-building-location - Location of the adresse in a building
floor (freq: 2) - Floor number in the building
unit - Unit in a building (e.g. "Apartment 5", "Suite 12")
unit-type - Type of a unit (e.g. "Apt", "Room", "Store")
unit-name (freq: 7) - Identifier of a unit (e.g. "5")
locality1 (freq: 484) - City/Suburb
admin-area1 (freq: 419) - Biggest type of admin area if a country has multiple levels
postal-code (freq: 482) - Postal code
postal-code-prefix - Postal code prefix
postal-code-suffix - Postal code suffix
country (freq: 327) - 2-letter country code
country-name - Name of a country
 
organization (freq: 237) - Name of an organization/company
 
credit-card - Artificial concept, not to be used in HTML
cc-name (freq: 174) - Full name of credit card holder
cc-given-name (freq: 3) - Given name of credit card holder
cc-additional-name - Additional name of credit card holder
cc-family-name (freq: 3) - Family name of credit card holder
cc-number (freq: 285) - Credit card number
cc-exp-MMYY (freq: 202) - Credit card expiration date in format MM/YY
cc-exp-MM (freq: 69) - Credit card expiration month (2 digits)
cc-exp-YY (freq: 23) - Credit card expiration date in format YY (2 digits)
cc-exp-MMYYYY (freq: 12) - Credit card expiration date in format MM/YYYY
cc-exp-MM (freq: 69) - Credit card expiration month (2 digits)
cc-exp-YYYY (freq: 49) - Credit card expiration date in format YYYY (4 digits)
cc-csc (freq: 287) - CSC/CVC/CVV number
cc-type (freq: 3) - Credit card type
 
tel (freq: 5) - Full telephone number
tel-country-code (freq: 20) - Country code component of the telephone number
tel-national (freq: 369) - Telephone number without the county code component, with a country-internal prefix applied if applicable
tel-area-code - Area code component of the telephone number, with a country-internal prefix applied if applicable
tel-local - Telephone number without the country code and area code components
tel-local-prefix - First part of the component of the telephone number that follows the area code, when that component is split into two components
tel-local-suffix - Second part of the component of the telephone number that follows the area code, when that component is split into two components
tel-extension - Telephone number internal extension code
 
email (freq: 191) - Email address
